  "prompt": "What are the business requirements to start a food truck business in Kenya?",
  "response": "To start a food truck business in Kenya, you'll need to comply with several business and legal requirements:\n\n1. Business Registration\n- Register your business with the Registrar of Companies\n- Obtain a business name/trading license\n- Register for tax purposes with Kenya Revenue Authority (KRA)\n- Get a Personal Identification Number (PIN)\n\n2. Food Safety and Health Regulations\n- Obtain a food handler's certificate\n- Get health clearance from County Health Department\n- Acquire food safety certification\n- Regular health inspections and food hygiene compliance\n\n3. Licenses and Permits\n- County business permit\n- Public health certificate\n- Food handling license\n- Parking/trading permit\n- Commercial vehicle registration\n- Health and safety compliance certificate\n\n4. Vehicle Requirements\n- Commercial truck/vehicle registration\n- Valid motor vehicle insurance\n- Roadworthy certificate\n- Specialized food truck modifications meeting health standards\n\n5. Financial Requirements\n- Business bank account\n- Initial capital investment\n- Working capital\n- Potential loan or financing\n\n6. Additional Considerations\n- Equipment and kitchen standards\n- Menu planning\n- Supplier contracts\n- Marketing strategy\n- Location/parking permissions\n\nConsulting local county authorities and Kenya Food and Drugs Authority (KFDA) for specific detailed requirements is recommended.",
